=== OpenRescue: Prepare India MBTiles ===
Data directory: /home/anbu/25_class/Sem_4/FOSS/OpenRescue/docker/tileserver/data
✓ Directory ensured: /home/anbu/25_class/Sem_4/FOSS/OpenRescue/docker/tileserver/data

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
 No MBTILES_URL environment variable set.
 To use the tileserver you need an MBTiles file.
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Option A — Download a pre-built MBTiles:
  export MBTILES_URL='https://your-url/india.mbtiles'
  bash scripts/prepare_mbtiles_india.sh

Option B — Generate from OpenMapTiles (advanced):
  1. Clone https://github.com/openmaptiles/openmaptiles
  2. Edit .env to set BBOX=68.11,6.55,97.40,35.67 (India)
  3. Run: make generate-bbox-file && make download area=india
  4. Run: make import-data && make generate-tiles-pg
  5. Copy the output .mbtiles to /home/anbu/25_class/Sem_4/FOSS/OpenRescue/docker/tileserver/data/india.mbtiles

Option C — Use Protomaps or similar:
  Visit https://protomaps.com/downloads/protomaps
  Create an India extract and download the .pmtiles/.mbtiles
  Place it at: /home/anbu/25_class/Sem_4/FOSS/OpenRescue/docker/tileserver/data/india.mbtiles

Once placed, run: bash scripts/start_tileserver.sh

